Cop shot in the face during police station shootout28 June 2017Cape Town - A brazen gunman opened fire in a Cape Town police station in the early hours of Wednesday morning, hitting a sergeant in the face.The officer has been admitted to hospital in a stable condition following the shootout in the Lingelethu West police station at 02:50.Provincial police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Andre Traut confirmed that three suspects had entered the station, ostensibly to report a robbery.&ldquo;One of the suspects produced a firearm and shot a police sergeant in his face. Police returned fire and the suspects fled,&rdquo; he said.The trio are yet to be arrested.News24